-- Chelsea Wants to Sign Racing Genk Winger, Express Says: Soccer Roundup
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2012-01-25T10:27:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-25/chelsea-wants-to-sign-racing-genk-winger-express-says-soccer-roundup.html
The following is a roundup of soccer
stories from U.K. newspapers, with clickable links to the Web.  Racing to Chelsea  Racing Genk winger Kevin de Bruyne may join Chelsea for 8.5
million pounds ($13 million), the  Daily Express  reported.  The London club would loan the 20-year-old Belgium national
team player back to Genk for the remainder of the season or the
year before joining Chelsea, the newspaper said.  Balotelli Brother on Trial  Sunderland is giving a tryout to Enoch Balotelli, the
younger brother of Manchester City striker  Mario Balotelli , the
 Daily Mirror  reported. Bosnian international striker Zlatan
Muslimovic is also on trial at the club.  Heskey is Free to Go  Aston Villa  may let Emile Heskey go for free this summer as
the club tries to cut down on its salary costs, the  Daily Mirror 
reported.  The 34-year-old former England player cost 3.5 million
pounds two years ago and is one of the club’s “top earners,”
the paper said.  Anton Won’t Shake Terry’s Hand  Queens Park Ranger player Anton Ferdinand won’t shake
Chelsea captain  John Terry ’s hand when the two meet in this
weekend’s F.A. Cup match, the  Daily Mirror  reported.  The Jan. 28 game marks the first time Terry will play at
Loftus Road since he was charged with racially abusing Ferdinand
during a game in October.  To contact the reporter on this story:
